Will all the @scungillisisters please stand up!? 🐚👯‍♀️⁣⁣
⁣⁣
One of our favorite family traditions is our 𝐂𝐡𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐦𝐚𝐬 𝐅𝐢𝐬𝐡 𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐚𝐝 extravaganza — a labor of love for the 𝐅𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐒𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐧 𝐅𝐢𝐬𝐡𝐞𝐬 🇮🇹 A family tradition that’s been alive for 𝘰𝘷𝘦𝘳 𝟾𝟶 𝘺𝘦𝘢𝘳𝘴, now spearheaded by our Uncle @jcerone3. This dish is our namesake ❤️⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Our family’s fish salad includes 🖐️ different seafoods: octopus 🐙, calamari, crab 🦀, shrimp 🦐 & last, but not least, 𝐒𝐂𝐔𝐍𝐆𝐈𝐋𝐋𝐈 (conch)! Seafood is boiled in a giant bath of bay leaves, black peppercorn, red chili peppers & salt. The salad comes together with lots of celery, lemon juice, EVOO, sliced garlic, lemon pepper, parsley & S+P. 𝘚𝘩𝘢𝘳𝘦 𝘺𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘧𝘢𝘮𝘪𝘭𝘺’𝘴 𝘧𝘢𝘷𝘰𝘳𝘪𝘵𝘦 𝘊𝘩𝘳𝘪𝘴𝘵𝘮𝘢𝘴 𝘵𝘳𝘢𝘥𝘪𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘪𝘯 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘤𝘰𝘮𝘮𝘦𝘯𝘵𝘴 👇🏽

New year, same tasty tradition! ✨🇬🇷 ⁣
⁣
Throughout the holidays, we overload on Italian food — it’s an 𝘢𝘣𝘣𝘰𝘯𝘥𝘢𝘯𝘻𝘢 — thus a 𝐆𝐫𝐞𝐞𝐤 𝐍𝐘𝐄 𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐧𝐞𝐫 𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐝𝐢𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 was born. This year’s dinner: @eatatandros 🏛️⁣
⁣
Some 𝐆𝐫𝐞𝐞𝐤 𝐡𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐥𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭𝐬 from the past:⁣
🇬🇷 @avli Taverna Style Lamb Chops ⁣
🇬🇷 @emachicago Hummus & Grilled Chicken Kebab⁣
🇬🇷 @taximchicago Krítis Peynirlí (Politiki-style Flatbread)⁣

Not pictured (but 𝘸𝘰𝘳𝘵𝘩 𝘮𝘦𝘯𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯𝘪𝘯𝘨): @lyragreek - see previous post for menu highlights ⁣
⁣
What’s your NYE dinner tradition? 🪩

First 🍕 of 2️⃣0️⃣2️⃣3️⃣! ⁣
𝘚𝘸𝘪𝘱𝘦 👉🏼 for her close-up. ⁣
⁣
@piecechicago is definitely one of our 𝐭𝐨𝐩 🖐️ 𝐟𝐚𝐯𝐨𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐞 𝐩𝐢𝐳𝐳𝐚𝐬 𝐢𝐧 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐠𝐨 — and now that @pizzachickenicecream has closed, it’s climbing the chart! If you haven’t tried it yet, add it to your 𝟸𝟶𝟸𝟹 𝘮𝘶𝘴𝘵-𝘵𝘳𝘺 🍕 𝘭𝘪𝘴𝘵!

Curing the back-to-work blues with 𝐑𝐢𝐠𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐧𝐢 𝐓𝐨𝐬𝐜𝐚𝐧𝐢 — one of our favorite Winter pastas 🍝 ⁣
⁣
This Tuscan-Umbrian dish has been a 𝘭𝘰𝘯𝘨-𝘵𝘪𝘮𝘦 𝘧𝘢𝘮𝘪𝘭𝘺 𝘧𝘢𝘷𝘰𝘳𝘪𝘵𝘦 and always reminds us of home 🏡 It’s heartier than your traditional #bolognese sauce & has a unique mix of spices that kicks it up a notch!⁣
⁣
𝐑𝐢𝐠𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐧𝐢 𝐓𝐨𝐬𝐜𝐚𝐧𝐢 ⁣
*1 Tbsp EVOO⁣
*1# Ground Beef⁣
*1/2 Yellow Onion, chopped fine⁣
*4 Cloves Garlic, smashed⁣
*1-2 stalks Celery, thinly chopped⁣
*Parsley⁣
*Salt & pepper⁣
*32oz Chopped Tomatoes ⁣
*8oz Tomato Sauce⁣
*1 tsp Allspice ⁣
*1 tsp Cinnamon⁣
*1 tsp Nutmeg⁣
⁣
1. Brown beef, add chopped onion + season with S&P; sauté until onions turn clear.⁣
2. Add celery and cook 2 mins, then add garlic + Parsley and cook until fragrant. ⁣
3. Add tomatoes and spices; bring to a boil, then turn down to simmer. ⁣
4. Now season to taste & continue to let simmer until oil comes to top of sauce.⁣
5. Serve over rigatoni & top with grated cheese.⁣
𝘉𝘶𝘰𝘯 𝘢𝘱𝘱𝘦𝘵𝘪𝘵𝘰! 🤌

Still making 𝘴𝘱𝘪𝘳𝘪𝘵𝘴 bright 🎄🍸⁣
⁣
@matchbox_bar is one of our 𝐟𝐚𝐯𝐨𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐞 𝐂𝐡𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐦𝐚𝐬 𝐛𝐚𝐫𝐬, but if you didn’t make it there during the holidays, it’s still full of #christmas 𝘴𝘱𝘪𝘳𝘪𝘵𝘴! 🥃⁣
⁣
It’s one of Chicago’s most iconic & intimate bars, and their staff is always the warmest! It was definitely a highlight to our 𝐁𝐥𝐮𝐞 𝐋𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐁𝐚𝐫 𝐂𝐫𝐚𝐰𝐥 (ft. @floydspubchicago, @greeneyelounge, @bluelineondamen)⁣ 
⁣
🍹𝐌𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐨𝐫𝐝𝐞𝐫: their famous margarita w/ a powdered sugar rim ⁣

🚨#TRUFFbestchicago pizza @professorpizza is leaving Humboldt Park for a new undisclosed location! 😢🍕🥇⁣
⁣
In June 2022, Chicagoans voted @professorpizza as the 𝐁𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐏𝐢𝐳𝐳𝐚 𝐢𝐧 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐠𝐨! This 𝘛𝘩𝘶𝘳𝘴𝘥𝘢𝘺 - 𝘚𝘢𝘵𝘶𝘳𝘥𝘢𝘺 will be your last chance to try it from @humboldtparkeatery 🏠⁣
We highly recommend his 𝐌𝐮𝐬𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐦 𝐋𝐞𝐞𝐤 𝐍𝐘 𝐩𝐢𝐞 & his Tavern Style pie! Can’t wait to see what’s in store for this champ! 🏆

CHICAGO RESTAURANT WEEK 2023 STARTS… in ☝️ week! ⁣

Happiness is… a brunch spread ✨⁣
⁣
#CBRChicago is 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘺𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘢𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘨𝘦 hotel brunch! They’ve taken typical menu items and bumped them 🆙 a notch! Like their Bloody Mary with Aquavit, Eggs Benedict with Lobster Meat -or- Sausage & Waffles with Habañero Maple Syrup 🔥 ⁣
⁣
Our 𝐟𝐚𝐯𝐨𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐞𝐬 included:⁣
🌟 𝐂𝐁𝐑 𝐒𝐦𝐚𝐬𝐡 𝐁𝐮𝐫𝐠𝐞𝐫 🍔: the perfectly juicy patties, sesame seed bun & bourbon caramelized onions make this a #winner.
🌟 𝐂𝐁𝐑 𝐁𝐥𝐮𝐞𝐛𝐞𝐫𝐫𝐲 𝐏𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐚𝐤𝐞𝐬 🫐: fluffy french toast-like pancakes exploding with juicy blueberries. ⁣
🌟 𝐋𝐨𝐛𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐁𝐞𝐧𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐜𝐭 🦞: a lighter cayenne hollandaise sauce is the best balance to the rich lobster meat. ⁣
🌟 𝐄𝐬𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐨 𝐌𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐢 🍸: featuring @lacolombecoffee espresso plus vanilla + hazelnut notes, this might be the best espresso martini in Chicago!⁣
⁣
Located inside @royalsonestarivernorth , CBR (aka Corn, Barley & Rye) is guaranteed to be the perfect destination for your upcoming Valentine’s Day and St. Patrick’s Day plans — or a cozy winter staycation ❄️⁣
⁣

The perfect dish doesn’t exis— 😍⁣
Cue the “𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞”: the best bowl-plate for your salads, grain bowls, pastas & more! 🥗⁣ 
⁣
@anthropologie has this 4-piece set on sale rn & we promise you won’t regret this purchase!

Looking for a good halfway point to meet your suburbian parents for dinner? Or just looking for some damn good seafood-focused Italian food? @ristoranteagostinogustofino hits the spot with their home style Southern Italian dishes (reservation & recommendations thanks to establishment regular @jacktouhy22 😜) 
⁣
The 𝐠𝐫𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐝 𝐦𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐚 covers all the bases to start off the meal (and they give you plenty of bread to soak up all the oil with) and the 𝐦𝐮𝐬𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐬 𝐦𝐚𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐫𝐚 come highly recommended, but we opted for the 𝐬𝐩𝐚𝐠𝐡𝐞𝐭𝐭𝐢 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐦𝐮𝐬𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐬 as our pasta dish instead 🤌🏼 followed by the 𝐠𝐫𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐝 𝐛𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐳𝐢𝐧𝐨 𝐟𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐢𝐝𝐞 andddd 👇🏼⁣
(Pro tip:) order the 𝐛𝐨𝐧𝐞-𝐢𝐧 𝐜𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐯𝐞𝐬𝐮𝐯𝐢𝐨 as soon as you sit down as it takes longer to cook and will be ready just in time to move onto your main course

Sunday morning routine: Workout class // Coffee shop ☕️Today’s lineup @doyourumble 🥊 and @nomadchicago 

Nomad is tucked away in River North off Franklin St (just north of Chicago Ave near Headquarters) and is filled with the cutest retail products - highly recommend stopping in if you need a nice gift for your galentines 💞

In 𝘲𝘶𝘦𝘴𝘰 you didn’t know… today is 𝐍𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐓𝐞𝐱𝐚𝐬 𝐃𝐚𝐲! 🤠🧀⁣
⁣
After spending the weekend in Fort Worth, I quickly realized that queso is definitely the 𝐮𝐧𝐨𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐜𝐢𝐚𝐥 𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐡 𝐨𝐟 𝐓𝐞𝐱𝐚𝐬! It is the epitome of #texmex 🇲🇽 and it’s dangerously delicious! ⁣
⁣
@palomasuerteftx by famous #fwtx @cheftimlove is ideally located behind @mulealley — overlooking the Stockyards River Walk. The fajitas & birria tacos looked insane, but we couldn’t pass up the 𝐛𝐮𝐢𝐥𝐝-𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫-𝐨𝐰𝐧 𝐭𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐪𝐮𝐞𝐬𝐨! (Step aside tableside guac, there’s a new sheriff in town 🤠)

📸 Say ‘Formaggio’! 🧀⁣
⁣
The Scungilli Squad (incl. scungilli cugini) visited @francescasmiomodo last night in St. Charles — it was def worth the trek from the city! It’s the 𝘰𝘭𝘥 𝘍𝘳𝘢𝘯𝘤𝘦𝘴𝘤𝘢’𝘴 *gorgeously rebranded*! We would 𝐝𝐞𝐟𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐭𝐞𝐥𝐲 𝐫𝐞𝐜𝐨𝐦𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐝 this spot for Valentine’s Day & can’t wait to go back! ⁣
⁣
What we ordered:⁣
✨ Focaccia Di Recco (a @scottharrishospitality staple)⁣
✨ Gianna’s Burrata ⁣
✨ Beet Salad⁣
✨ Italian Chopped Salad⁣
✨ Spaghetti Frutti Di Mare ⁣
✨ Agnolotti Tartufi ⁣
✨ Mafalde Lamb Bolognese ⁣
✨ Paccheri Cacio e Pepe 🆕⁣
✨ Radiatori Prosciutto e Piselli 🆕⁣
(More like, 𝘸𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘥𝘪𝘥𝘯’𝘵 𝘸𝘦 𝘰𝘳𝘥𝘦𝘳!) ⁣
⁣
We washed it all down with pistachio gelato (topped with a ♥️-shaped pizzelle) and chocolate martini shots courtesy of @chefpeterderuvo5 🥰

𝐇𝐀𝐏𝐏𝐘 𝐍𝐀𝐓𝐈𝐎𝐍𝐀𝐋 𝐏𝐈𝐙𝐙𝐀 𝐃𝐀𝐘 😊🍕!!!⁣
⁣
Celebrate with @nancyspizza Half Off Thin Crust Pizza deal today - 𝘸𝘦 𝘳𝘦𝘤𝘰𝘮𝘮𝘦𝘯𝘥 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘚𝘶𝘱𝘦𝘳 𝘛𝘩𝘪𝘯 🔥 Also, when you download the Nancy’s Pizza app and sign up as a rewards member you get a free small thin cheese pizza (w/ the purchase of an app - we went 𝐛𝐨𝐨𝐦 𝐛𝐨𝐨𝐦 𝐰𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐬 😋) ⁣
⁣
Nancy’s was founded by the inventors of Chicago’s original stuffed pizza - inspired by the classic Italian Easter Pie back in the 70s!

Our kind of halftime show🚶🏻‍♀️🌮⁣
⁣
This is your sign to have a 𝗪𝐚𝐥𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐓𝐚𝐜𝐨 𝐁𝐚𝐫 at your next party! We really love anything with a “bar” involved, but this hit the spot! Shoutout to the hosts who had 𝘢𝘭𝘭𝘭𝘭𝘭𝘭𝘭 the right toppings — down to the Valentina 🔥⁣
⁣
 I already miss @badgalriri, but I 𝐦𝐢𝐬𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐦𝐨𝐫𝐞.
𝘚𝘢𝘺 𝘩𝘦𝘭𝘭𝘰 𝘵𝘰 𝘮𝘺 𝘭𝘪𝘵𝘵𝘭𝘦 𝘧𝘳𝘪𝘦𝘯𝘥 👉🏼 the 𝐏𝐚𝐜𝐢𝐧𝐨 from @nonnaschicago

We never met a paczki we didn’t like 🍩⁣
⁣
𝐇𝐚𝐩𝐩𝐲 𝐌𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐢 𝐆𝐫𝐚𝐬! 💜💚 Year after year, our amazing coworkers order King Cake straight from NOLA & boxes of paczki from the 𝘣𝘦𝘴𝘵 Chicago bakeries. ⁣
⁣
If you failed to preorder and can’t find any bakeries in stock, many grocery stores including @marianosmarket & @costco are carrying @stansdonutschicago strawberry + Bavarian crème paczkis! #rundontwalk

Our bride shines bright in a room full of sparklers ✨🪩⁣
⁣
This Miami Bachelorette dinner at @chicarestaurants was one of the 𝐛𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐠𝐫𝐨𝐮𝐩 𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞𝐬 I’ve ever had! From the complimentary welcome drink, through all the delicious courses, to the live entertainment🔥— 𝘊𝘩𝘪𝘤𝘢 𝘥𝘰𝘦𝘴 𝘪𝘵 𝘢𝘭𝘭! Our planner organized an 8-dish family style meal with cocktails & everything was a hit! Still dreaming of the ginger chili sauce 🤤 𝐓𝐢𝐩: make a 9pm or later reso for optimal entertainment 💃

Gotta get down on 𝘧𝘳𝘺-day 🍟⁣
⁣
I stand by my claim that @allrisebrewing has some of the 𝐛𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐟𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐬 𝐢𝐧 📍𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐠𝐨! Seasoned well, soft on the inside & perfectly crispy outside! We love a brewery that not only makes good beer, but takes food seriously — that’s definitely All Rise! ⁣
⁣
Looking forward to sunny days on their patio very soon! ☀️

There ain’t no Friday like a 𝐅𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐒𝐪𝐮𝐚𝐫𝐞𝐝 𝐅𝐫𝐢𝐝𝐚𝐲 🍕🎉⁣
⁣
Do what we do 👉🏼 Order a 𝐌𝐢𝐱 ‘𝐧’ 𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡 𝐛𝐨𝐱 — 2 vegetarian slices plus 2 meat slices. Eat 2 for #LentFriday and save 2 for the weekend! These slices are 𝘣𝘪𝘨𝘨𝘦𝘳 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘯 𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘺 𝘢𝘱𝘱𝘦𝘢𝘳! 👀 Their Take ‘n’ Bake concept makes it easy to eat whenever your busy weekend allows! ⁣
⁣
𝐏𝐢𝐜𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞𝐝 📸: Tie Dye, Spacca, Buffalo Cauliflower (🆕) & Italian Meatball (🆕)⁣
⬆️ Both of their new pies blew us away! 🙌🔥

Corned beef shamrocks our world
 🥩🍀⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The @tumanstap #stpatricksday specials are 🌟 gold!  Their juicy 𝐒𝐰𝐢𝐬𝐬 & 𝐂𝐨𝐫𝐧𝐞𝐝 𝐁𝐞𝐞𝐟 sammie is a guilty pleasure! If you missed yesterday — tonight and Friday are your 𝘭𝘢𝘴𝘵 𝘤𝘩𝘢𝘯𝘤𝘦𝘴 to indulge! Until next year! 🇮🇪
*slams laptop shut til Monday* 🍀🍻

You say St. Patrick’s Day < we say St. Joseph’s Day! 🇮🇹🍝⁣
⁣
Tomorrow (March 19) is 𝐒𝐭. 𝐉𝐨𝐬𝐞𝐩𝐡’𝐬 𝐃𝐚𝐲! The 𝘐𝘵𝘢𝘭𝘪𝘢𝘯 𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘴𝘪𝘰𝘯 of SPD. Last year, we made a simple tomato-based Anchovy & Breadcrumb pasta, but we stepped it up a notch with this 𝐒𝐩𝐚𝐠𝐡𝐞𝐭𝐭𝐢 𝐜𝐨𝐧 𝐋𝐞 𝐒𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐞 🐟 The umami flavors and the crunchy texture of the breadcrumbs make this dish MVP (𝘮𝘰𝘴𝘵 𝘷𝘢𝘭𝘶𝘢𝘣𝘭𝘦 𝘱𝘢𝘴𝘵𝘢) of #stjosephsday 🏆 ⁣
⁣
𝐒𝐩𝐚𝐠𝐡𝐞𝐭𝐭𝐢 𝐜𝐨𝐧 𝐋𝐞 𝐒𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐞 (for 2)⁣
⁣
For pasta:⁣
*2T EVOO⁣
*1/2 Yellow Onion, finely diced⁣
*2 cloves of Garlic, thinly sliced⁣
*1T Anchovy Paste⁣
*1-1/2T Tomato Paste⁣
*3 Sardines, skinned, deboned & finely chopped⁣
*Handful of Fennel Fronds, chopped⁣
*Pasta Water⁣
*1/2lb Spaghetti⁣
*Garnish: toasted breadcrumbs ⁣
⁣
1. Heat EVOO over medium heat, add onions and sauté until translucent. ⁣
2. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, then add anchovy paste and mix well. ⁣
3. Add tomato paste and mix until fully incorporated.⁣
4. Toss in sardines and fennel fronds; cook a few min. ⁣
5. Cook pasta and reserve some pasta water for sauce. Add pasta to sauce and add pasta water one ladle at a time until sauce is silky. ⁣
6. Plate and garnish with toasted breadcrumbs 🤌

Listen up mothacluckas 🐔 let’s get 𝘣𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘥-y to conquer the week with our latest meal prep addiction: 𝐁𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐞𝐝 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐬𝐞𝐫𝐯𝐞𝐝 🖐🏼 𝐰𝐚𝐲𝐬👩🏻‍🍳⁣
⁣
These breaded cutlets are the easiest & tastiest way to get ahead before the week hits. Whether you’re prepping for lunch or dinner, here’s our fool proof chicken cutlet recipe & 5 delicious combos! ⁣
⁣
𝐁𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐞𝐝 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐂𝐮𝐭𝐥𝐞𝐭𝐬 ⁣
*Boneless Chicken (if using breasts, slice in half for thinner pieces)⁣
*Salt & Pepper⁣
*Flour⁣
*2 Eggs per lb (whisked with chopped parsley & grated parmigiana)⁣
*Breadcrumbs (homemade, Panko, store bought, etc) mixed with sesame seeds 🔑⁣
*Light Frying Oil⁣
*Sea Salt⁣
⁣
1. Pound chicken out very thin (use meat pounder or rolling pin or even your cast iron skillet). ⁣
2. Season both sides generously with salt & pepper.⁣
3. Dust chicken in flour, dunk in egg mixture, then coat in breadcrumb mixture. ⁣
4. Refrigerate for 30 min before frying. **this is key to the breading sticking well after frying⁣
5. Heat oil in cast iron skillet on medium heat, cook each side for ~2min (or until brown) then remove & sprinkle over sea salt. ⁣
⁣

It’s a great way to clear fresh garden veggies out of the fridge 🥑🍅🌽 We’ve also been on a rotisserie chicken kick (a $4.99 @costco chicken results in so many different meals), so we shredded some & tossed it in chipotle sauce! The leftovers make awesome shredded chicken nachos too! ⁣

𝘚/𝘰 𝘵𝘰 @goebbertsfarm 𝘧𝘰𝘳 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘣𝘦𝘴𝘵 𝘧𝘳𝘦𝘴𝘩 𝘴𝘸𝘦𝘦𝘵 𝘤𝘰𝘳𝘯 🌽 ⁣
⁣
𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐁𝐞𝐚𝐧𝐬 𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐞:⁣
*1 lb Black Beans (canned or dry)⁣
*2 cloves Garlic (minced)⁣
*1/4 C Yellow Onion (minced)⁣
*1 Bay Leaf⁣
*1 T EVOO⁣
*Salt, to taste⁣

⁣
After rinsing beans, throw all ingredients into pot, cover and boil. Then remove cover and simmer until beans are tender - add broth if it starts drying out. Simmer canned beans for ~10min while dry beans should simmer for ~1.5hrs.

𝐂𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐬𝐢𝐜 𝐂𝐫𝐨𝐜𝐤𝐩𝐨𝐭 𝐓𝐮𝐫𝐤𝐞𝐲 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐥𝐢⁣
* 1# Ground Turkey⁣
* 1/2 White Onion, chopped⁣
* 1 Green Pepper, chopped⁣
* 3 Garlic cloves, minced⁣
* 15oz Crushed Tomatoes⁣
* 15oz Tomato Sauce⁣
* 15oz Fire Roasted Diced Tomatoes⁣
* 15oz Kidney Beans, rinsed & drained⁣
* 1/2C Homemade Chicken Broth, unsalted (𝘴𝘦𝘦 “𝘣𝘳𝘰𝘵𝘩” 𝘩𝘪𝘨𝘩𝘭𝘪𝘨𝘩𝘵𝘴)⁣
* 1/2T Organic Better Than Bouillon Chicken Base⁣
* 1T Coconut Aminos⁣
* 1-1/2T Chili Powder⁣
* 1/2T Cumin⁣
* 1t Oregano⁣
* 1/2t Smoked Paprika⁣
* 1/4t Ground Pepper⁣
* 1 Bay Leaf⁣
* Salt to Taste (we used a pinch when sautéing the veggies and didn’t need any more)⁣
* Garnish Preferences: Cilantro, Avocado, Jalapeño, Shredded Mexican Cheese, Saltines, Hot Sauce, Pumpkin Seeds, Greek Yogurt⁣
⁣
1. Cook the veggies in the crockpot on “sauté” until soft, then add ground Turkey and cook until brown. ⁣
2. Add all other ingredients into pot — mix well. ⁣
3. Cook on “Slow Cook - Low” for 6-8 hours, then mix & season to taste (we didn’t need to add anything more). ⁣
4. Serve with garnishes & dig in*! ⁣
*We recommend cooking this 1 day before you’re going to serve it for best taste!⁣
⁣

@friendsstationchicago is the OG 𝐀𝐘𝐂𝐄 𝐑𝐨𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐲 𝐇𝐨𝐭𝐩𝐨𝐭 𝐢𝐧 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐠𝐨 and we tried their new top-quality menu items 🤩 If you’re new to hotpot, or not a seasoned pro, this spot makes it a super approachable experience! And if you don’t want to share, 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘥𝘰𝘯’𝘵 𝘩𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘵𝘰 — the personal hotpots allow you to customize based on your preferences & nobody else’s! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣

𝐄𝐬𝐜𝐚𝐫𝐨𝐥𝐞 & 𝐁𝐞𝐚𝐧𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐒𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐚𝐠𝐞⁣
-2 Heads Escarole, rinsed well & chopped⁣

-3 Cloves Garlic, sliced thin⁣

-EVOO⁣
-Crushed Red Pepper Flakes⁣
-1-2C Vegetable Broth (add more if you prefer it soupier)⁣

2. Add sausage and cook until brown. ⁣
3. Deglaze bottom of the pan with some vegetable broth, add in beans and escarole, and cover. ⁣
4. Cook down for a few minutes (until escarole is wilted) and add more vegetable broth until your desired consistency is met. ⁣
5. Mix in grated cheese and season to taste. ⁣

⁣
𝗪𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐡 𝐟𝐥𝐚𝐯𝐨𝐫 𝐢𝐬 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐟𝐚𝐯𝐨𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐞?!

Chicago Restaurant Week 2024 restaurant lists and menus are OUT! Start planning how you’re going to eat your way through Chicago’s winter months at @choosechicago. ⁣
⁣
One of our favorite restaurant week spots is @abarestaurant. They’re one of the few menus that start you off with a beverage (they even have a N/A option for those participating in #dryjanuary) 🍸 Definitely recommend dining with at least 3 people to get the most variety - you will leave very full & happy 😋 ⁣
⁣

SO PROUD of @ramen__lord’s successful opening of @akahoshiramen 🍜(!!!) as if we have any connection to his work, but we’re just 2 fangirls that have been following his journey via ➡️ IGs of at-home experimentation, local popups, and educational travels 🇯🇵 ⁣
